    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Peel your<strong> potatoes</strong> and chop them into quarters, then add to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herb-crusted-roast-pork-with-apple-sauce-and-garlicky-gravy/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel, core and roughly chop your <strong>apple[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped apple </strong>to a separate pot with a lid with 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [125ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, over a medium heat for 10-12 min or until the apple has softened, stirring occasionally</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>softened apple</strong> to a bowl with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>apple sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herb-crusted-roast-pork-with-apple-sauce-and-garlicky-gravy/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely on the diagonal</p><p>Chop your<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>herby crumb</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herb-crusted-roast-pork-with-apple-sauce-and-garlicky-gravy/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, drain the<strong> potatoes</strong> (save the pot!) and shake them around a colander to fluff up the edges</p><p>Add the <strong>fluffed potatoes</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 10 min</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herb-crusted-roast-pork-with-apple-sauce-and-garlicky-gravy/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had 10 min, add the <strong>sliced carrots</strong> and <strong>halved green beans </strong>to the tray with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 10 min</p><p>Meanwhile, crush your<strong> garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and remove the skin</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herb-crusted-roast-pork-with-apple-sauce-and-garlicky-gravy/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> with the <strong>crushed garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened, then set aside for later \u2013 this is your<strong> garlic-infused gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herb-crusted-roast-pork-with-apple-sauce-and-garlicky-gravy/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the gravy is thickening, top your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> with the<strong> herby crumb</strong></p><p>Tip: Press the crumb into the pork steaks firmly with your hands to help it stick!</p><p>Once the veg has had 10 min, add the <strong>herb-crusted pork steak[s]</strong> to the tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 13-15 min or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herb-crusted-roast-pork-with-apple-sauce-and-garlicky-gravy/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>garlic-infused gravy</strong> to the hob to reheat</p><p>Serve the <strong>herb-crusted roast pork</strong> with the<strong> roast potatoes</strong>, <strong>carrots</strong> and <strong>green beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Serve with a dollop of<strong> apple sauce</strong> and pour the<strong> garlic-infused gravy</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
